## 2. Operational Pipelines (How the System Works)

The "Idea Pipeline" of how entities flow through the system is structured into four main operational pipelines:

### **A. Customer Onboarding & AMC Pipeline**
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Add Customer] --> B{Service Type?}
    B -->|AMC| C[Create AMC Contract]
    B -->|Monthly| D[Standard Billing Profile]
    C --> E[Set SLA & Monthly Hours]
```
*   **Flow**: A `Customer` is registered in the system. If they have an AMC, a `ContractAMC` record is created defining their monthly allotted hours and priorities. 

### **B. Ticket Lifecycle Pipeline**
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Ticket Created] --> B[Assigned to Agent]
    B --> C[Status: In Progress]
    C --> D[Agent Adds Comments]
    D --> E[Agent Logs Work Time]
    E --> F[Status: Resolved]
```
*   **Flow**: A client or agent creates a `Ticket`. An `Agent` is assigned. The agent works on it, records communication in `TicketComment`, tracks time via `WorkLog`, and eventually resolves the ticket.

### **C. Billing & Invoicing Pipeline**
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[WorkLogs Accumulated] --> B[End of Month]
    B --> C[Calculate Hours Used]
    C --> D{Exceeds AMC Hours?}
    D -->|Yes| E[Bill Overage at Hourly Rate]
    D -->|No| F[No Extra Charge]
    E --> G[Generate Invoice]
    F --> G
```
*   **Flow**: All `WorkLog` entries for a customer are aggregated in a `Billing` cycle. It checks against `ContractAMC.monthly_hours`. Invoices are generated for the surplus or standard monthly rate.

### **D. AI Assistance Pipeline**
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[AI Triggered] --> B[Backend /ai Route]
    B --> C[LLM Processing Gemini/OpenRouter]
    C --> D[Response generation / Ticket classification]
```

